1
00:00:11,660 --> 00:00:14,240
[January 15, 1988]

2
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:42,790
What's wrong?

3
00:00:48,110 --> 00:00:49,030
You know you're about to give birth.

4
00:00:49,030 --> 00:00:51,360
You shouldn't have come with us this time.

5
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:55,200
[Chief of Fengmao Village, Mou Haidong]

6
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:05,069
Be careful with that.

7
00:01:05,069 --> 00:01:06,130
Alright, let's go.

8
00:01:11,340 --> 00:01:13,270
Why is she giving birth on the boat?

9
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:15,970
Dong!

10
00:01:16,050 --> 00:01:17,660
Dong, there are police!

11
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:25,150
Captain Fang, that boat looks suspicious.

12
00:01:25,150 --> 00:01:26,880
Please stop your vessel for inspection!

13
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:28,490
Start the boat! Hurry!

14
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:30,750
Please stop your vessel for inspection!

15
00:01:30,750 --> 00:01:32,110
Hurry up! Speed up!

16
00:01:32,770 --> 00:01:34,930
Faster! Go! Go!

17
00:01:35,509 --> 00:01:37,770
Please stop your vessel for inspection.

18
00:01:37,820 --> 00:01:38,039
[Captain of Narcotics Control Brigade
of Nanzhou City,
Fang Jianwei]

19
00:01:38,039 --> 00:01:39,550
Speed: 25 knots.

20
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,000
Please stop your vessel for inspection.

21
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:42,530
Catch up with them quickly.

22
00:01:43,590 --> 00:01:44,720
They'll catch up soon.

23
00:01:44,720 --> 00:01:45,950
Dong, what should we do?

24
00:01:45,950 --> 00:01:47,640
Please stop your vessel for inspection.

25
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,710
Hurry!

26
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,259
Please stop your vessel for inspection.

27
00:01:51,970 --> 00:01:53,080
Did you see that?

28
00:01:58,259 --> 00:01:59,660
Someone fell overboard.

29
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,050
Let's rescue her first.

30
00:02:05,950 --> 00:02:07,740
Contact the rescue boat immediately,

31
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:09,000
and tell them to hurry.

32
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,140
Miss,

33
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:28,880
please send a message for me.

34
00:02:31,760 --> 00:02:32,630
She died.

35
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:35,380
She passed away
shortly after giving birth.

36
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,030
Wu Jianguo.

37
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:42,600
Congratulations on becoming a father!
Both mother and baby are doing well.

38
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:42,750
[Yang Yipeng, a member of
Narcotics Control Brigade of Nanzhou]

39
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:44,920
The delivery went well. It's a girl.

40
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,400
You wife has given birth?

41
00:02:50,190 --> 00:02:50,430
Have you chosen a name?

42
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:52,890
[Captain of Narcotics Control
Brigade in Nanzhou, Wu Jianguo]

43
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,520
I discussed it with her

44
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:56,110
that if it was a girl,

45
00:02:56,310 --> 00:02:57,710
we would name her Zhi'an.

46
00:03:00,390 --> 00:03:01,900
Look how small he is,

47
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,770
but his crying is quite loud.

48
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,520
What's the point of keeping him?

49
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,510
Who's going to raise him?

50
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:07,560
Just throw him away.

51
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,210
Dong.

52
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:10,110
His mother took the blow for us.

53
00:03:10,660 --> 00:03:11,930
Just let him

54
00:03:12,310 --> 00:03:13,780
fight for his future.

55
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,200
You'll never make it big.

56
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:17,900
Don't follow me anymore.

57
00:03:20,290 --> 00:03:21,110
You know what?

58
00:03:21,620 --> 00:03:23,670
You're just a burden.

59
00:03:24,460 --> 00:03:26,320
We'll call you Duozai from now on.

60
00:03:26,890 --> 00:03:30,100
[Hunting]

61
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:32,579
[Episode 1]

62
00:03:32,970 --> 00:03:35,350
[Year 2010]

63
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,840
Hao, I'm going to work
at the fish market first.

64
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,030
Later, come with me to the car dealership

65
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,270
to order the car.

66
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:46,040
Duozai, you've saved up
the money so quickly!

67
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:46,920
Awesome!

68
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:48,570
It's nothing special.

69
00:03:48,930 --> 00:03:51,100
See you at the dealership.
Don't bail on me.

70
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:51,980
Got it?

71
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:58,380
♪ The path of life
is winding and tortuous ♪

72
00:04:02,950 --> 00:04:07,890
♪ The ocean's moods are hard to foresee ♪

73
00:04:12,570 --> 00:04:17,300
♪ Even if I've been through
happiness and hardships ♪

74
00:04:20,810 --> 00:04:27,910
♪  Life, life ♪

75
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:33,870
♪  I want to go far away alone ♪

76
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,470
♪  Wealth and poverty are all fate ♪

77
00:04:40,330 --> 00:04:43,490
♪  The tides are predestined ♪

78
00:04:45,290 --> 00:04:46,680
♪ A wretched soul partings
and reunions,
joys and sorrows ♪

79
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:50,020
[Gold Award]

80
00:04:50,020 --> 00:04:53,190
♪ We must see right from wrong ♪

81
00:04:54,550 --> 00:04:57,830
♪ Why wake up when there's wine today? ♪

82
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:02,590
♪ It's hard to buy the youth ♪

83
00:05:04,780 --> 00:05:10,040
♪ Life, life ♪

84
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,250
I'm leaving, Mom. I'll be late.

85
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:12,480
[A team member of
Narcotics Control Brigade
of Nanzhou City, Wu Zhi'an]

86
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,270
Be sure to stay safe
once you're on the team.

87
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:15,240
Safety, safety. I'll be careful.

88
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,560
Got it. I'm going now.

89
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,830
You haven't had breakfast yet.

90
00:05:17,830 --> 00:05:18,600
Bye-bye.

91
00:06:56,610 --> 00:06:58,320
Driving a truck these days

92
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:00,390
can earn you over 10,000 a month.

93
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:03,130
So, you want to be a truck driver too?

94
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:05,790
I'll make more money than him
if I can be one.

95
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,120
I'm so close to making
over 10,000 a month.

96
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,540
All I need is one truck.

97
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:09,560
Great.

98
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,010
If you hit that black wire,

99
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:15,040
I'll give you 10 yuan.

100
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:16,000
Gambling again?

101
00:07:16,210 --> 00:07:17,360
If I can hit that black wire,

102
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,050
we'll have a chicken leg
for dinner tonight.

103
00:07:19,050 --> 00:07:21,150
You'll get fined
for throwing things from up high.

104
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:23,070
Life is as vast as the ocean.
Just be happy.

105
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:25,070
You lead such a boring life. Come on.

106
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:28,210
Where did they all go?

107
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:31,070
After facial recognition comparison,

108
00:07:31,070 --> 00:07:32,390
he has a prior drug-related offense,

109
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:34,680
and has been under our close surveillance.

110
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:35,190
Okay.

111
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:37,490
Hello.

112
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,100
Who are you looking for?

113
00:07:39,100 --> 00:07:40,630
I'm here to report for duty.

114
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:42,040
[Lin Qiong, a member of
Narcotics Control Brigade of Nanzhou]

115
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:44,130
Have you met the new colleague?

116
00:07:44,159 --> 00:07:46,920
This is Zhi'an.
She's here to help
from the Cyber Police Unit.

117
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,670
No need to salute in plain clothes.

118
00:07:48,670 --> 00:07:48,990
[Wang Zixian, a member of
Narcotics Control Brigade of Nanzhou]

119
00:07:48,990 --> 00:07:49,800
I'm Wang Zixian.

120
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:50,830
Hello.

121
00:07:51,430 --> 00:07:52,360
[Chief of Narcotics Control Brigade
of Nanzhou City, Luo Zhongkui]

122
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,870
Who is she?

123
00:07:54,130 --> 00:07:54,250
[Cherish Life, Reject Drugs.]

124
00:07:54,250 --> 00:07:55,650
Her father is Wu Jianguo.

125
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:57,800
Got it, thanks.

126
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:01,750
Mr. Xin

127
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:03,950
didn't want to sell it to you so cheaply.

128
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:05,120
It's for my sake.

129
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:06,720
He sold it to you for 30,000.

130
00:08:08,130 --> 00:08:10,260
I know it's all because of
your fluence, Lili.

131
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:11,990
I'll treat you to dinner later.

132
00:08:39,010 --> 00:08:41,350
The final payment of 20,000
must be settled in three days,

133
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:42,330
Boss Duozai.

134
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:43,940
No problem.

135
00:08:45,610 --> 00:08:48,450
Now that you have a car,
it really shows how things are different.

136
00:08:48,450 --> 00:08:50,630
You even called him 'Boss' Duozai.

137
00:08:50,910 --> 00:08:52,200
Buzz off.

138
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:13,480
The weather is so nice today,

139
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,370
go get some sunshine and calcium.

140
00:09:16,550 --> 00:09:18,240
I need to make money.

141
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:25,870
I've got to go.

142
00:09:27,490 --> 00:09:29,070
You haven't paid yet.

143
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:32,420
How come you always act like this?

144
00:09:32,420 --> 00:09:34,660
I'll treat you to karaoke next time .

145
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,940
That'll make up for it.

146
00:09:36,690 --> 00:09:38,200
We'll settle everything
at the end of the year.

147
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,120
Don't come to my place next time.

148
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,030
What, can't bear to see me go?
Shall we do the dramatic farewell?

149
00:09:42,030 --> 00:09:43,200
So annoying.

150
00:10:58,510 --> 00:10:59,410
Did you get it?

151
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,440
Who delivered the goods to me today?

152
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:03,360
The guy who gave you the goods is Uncle Ma.

153
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,360
I've always gotten my stuff from him.

154
00:11:05,360 --> 00:11:06,780
No problem. Don't worry.

155
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,180
It's very safe.

156
00:11:09,930 --> 00:11:11,510
Where does he get his goods from?

157
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:12,150
His goods?

158
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:13,200
All the goods in this area

159
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,870
are sourced from Gold-Tooth Wan.

160
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:16,120
What's wrong?

161
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:26,650
[Wan's Mahjong Hall]

162
00:11:31,770 --> 00:11:37,150
[Wan's Mahjong Hall]

163
00:11:40,780 --> 00:11:43,980
♪ What is life for? ♪

164
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:49,530
♪Sometimes we are happy,
sometimes we need to win ♪

165
00:11:51,630 --> 00:11:54,490
♪ What is life for? ♪

166
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:59,770
♪ Sometimes we're partners
and sometimes we'll be apart  ♪

167
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:05,240
♪ Coming and going, worries and fears ♪

168
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,320
The machine's broken?

169
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,380
No, it's working.

170
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:11,230
♪ The good will lose, the bad will win ♪

171
00:12:12,760 --> 00:12:16,760
♪ Life, life ♪

172
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:21,350
♪ Talking of love, debating reason,
lamenting with a heart-wrenching regret ♪

173
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,360
You hit me!

174
00:12:40,590 --> 00:12:42,320
Are you blind?

175
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,070
You hit me! Don't you see?

176
00:12:44,090 --> 00:12:44,960
Stop yelling!

177
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:45,440
Get out!

178
00:12:45,470 --> 00:12:46,540
Don't knock on it!

179
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,350
Why shouldn't I?

180
00:12:47,350 --> 00:12:49,080
Hey, you crushed into my car!
Didn't you see it?

181
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:50,210
Get out of there now!

182
00:12:50,670 --> 00:12:51,880
You must be blind!

183
00:12:53,530 --> 00:12:55,300
You hit someone and won't even get out?

184
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:56,410
It was just an accident!

185
00:12:56,410 --> 00:12:56,960
Don't make excuses!

186
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:58,010
There are so many people and cars here.

187
00:12:58,010 --> 00:12:59,530
-It's so chaotic on the wharf.
-Lower your voice.

188
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:00,720
Stop shouting! What are you yelling for?

189
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,370
What do you want?

190
00:13:01,370 --> 00:13:01,980
Is it money you're after?

191
00:13:01,980 --> 00:13:03,350
What, are you going to pay for it?

192
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:05,160
I can't afford to pay.

193
00:13:06,700 --> 00:13:08,100
He's really beating him!

194
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:13,900
You want a slap?

195
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:15,510
Go ahead, slap me.

196
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:24,320
You all saw it, he asked me to hit him.

197
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,200
I didn't start it.

198
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:27,250
He said 'slap me', so I did.

199
00:13:30,490 --> 00:13:31,620
You actually hit me.

200
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,080
Why didn't you dodge?

201
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:34,050
Don't call the police.

202
00:13:34,050 --> 00:13:35,010
Quiet down.

203
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,720
Quiet down. Don't call the police.

204
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,580
I said no police! Don't call them!

205
00:13:39,300 --> 00:13:41,160
Take him to the hospital quickly.

206
00:13:43,110 --> 00:13:44,460
Tonight,

207
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:45,960
we drink till we drop!

208
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,240
Come on.

209
00:13:49,050 --> 00:13:49,840
That's right.

210
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,290
Ours is

211
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:53,050
a friendship born of conflict.

212
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,300
You mean this.

213
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,110
It's nothing. No big deal.

214
00:13:57,610 --> 00:13:58,310
Also,

215
00:13:58,970 --> 00:14:00,580
if you run into any trouble on this dock,

216
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:02,470
just drop my name.

217
00:14:02,490 --> 00:14:03,720
Zhen.

218
00:14:03,820 --> 00:14:04,620
My name works.

219
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,260
Zhen, come on.

220
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:07,370
I toast to you.

221
00:14:07,370 --> 00:14:08,720
Come on, let's clink glasses.

222
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:09,600
Alright.

223
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,650
I'm Ma Yong.

224
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,390
You can also call me Uncle Ma.

225
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:19,350
So now we know each other.

226
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:21,150
You're Uncle Ma?

227
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:22,310
Yes, that's right.

228
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:24,440
I've heard your name before.

229
00:14:25,420 --> 00:14:28,020
I do have some reputation
in this trade circle.

230
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,290
Uncle Ma,

231
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,800
you're a known name in this circle.

232
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:35,250
I've gone beyond that circle

233
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,380
for a long time.

234
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:37,170
No way.

235
00:14:37,190 --> 00:14:38,520
Since when? Yesterday?

236
00:14:39,070 --> 00:14:41,280
You've been in this business
for so many years.

237
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:43,540
It's impossible to be beyond the circle.

238
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:45,580
I just toe the line

239
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:47,340
and be an honest man.

240
00:14:47,370 --> 00:14:48,900
That's very good.

241
00:14:51,250 --> 00:14:52,160
Uncle Ma,

242
00:14:52,930 --> 00:14:53,620
well...

243
00:14:53,650 --> 00:14:55,180
You know when to advance and retreat.

244
00:14:55,180 --> 00:14:56,580
That kind of perspective

245
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:58,220
is better than most people's.

246
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:59,320
Look at my gray hair.

247
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:00,530
So much of it.

248
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:02,450
I'm too old for this business now.

249
00:15:02,790 --> 00:15:03,830
I understand.

250
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,410
You know, I've

251
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,700
been in this circle for three years.

252
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:11,680
Uncle Ma,

253
00:15:12,160 --> 00:15:14,840
if you ever want to make a comeback
in the future,

254
00:15:14,870 --> 00:15:15,690
come find me.

255
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:16,720
Alright.

256
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,720
I'm getting old.

257
00:15:18,830 --> 00:15:19,770
I can't keep up anymore.

258
00:15:19,770 --> 00:15:20,730
You can, actually.

259
00:15:20,730 --> 00:15:21,930
Not up for it anymore.

260
00:15:31,560 --> 00:15:33,770
I Gotta run. Something just popped up!

261
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:36,140
Didn't we just order food and drinks?

262
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:37,470
A few more minutes won't hurt.

263
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:38,610
Can't help it.

264
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:39,860
Got to make money now.

265
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:40,720
You know?

266
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,010
No choice.

267
00:15:42,030 --> 00:15:43,370
Making money is important.

268
00:15:43,370 --> 00:15:45,230
With money, life won't be so hard.

269
00:15:46,020 --> 00:15:47,110
Yes.

270
00:15:48,310 --> 00:15:50,580
Guess we owe ourselves a little ceremony, huh?

271
00:15:50,580 --> 00:15:51,460
Come.

272
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,690
Let's do a cross-arm toast.

273
00:15:55,690 --> 00:15:57,210
Alright, I see.

274
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:07,800
Duozai.

275
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:08,550
